    {
        "content": "<p>madsmtm submitted <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13137#pullrequestreview-4143130833\">PR review</a>.</p>",
        "id": 588472754,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1776715877
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>madsmtm created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13137#discussion_r3113385475\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I considered that, but there are no default flags for (<code>SectionKind::Data</code>, <code>SectionKind::ReadOnlyData</code> and <code>SectionKind::ReadOnlyDataWithRel</code>), and if there were, it would break if we tried to <code>|=</code> the section type.</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 588472758,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1776715877
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>bjorn3 submitted <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13137#pullrequestreview-4143151498\">PR review</a>.</p>",
        "id": 588473230,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
